<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1246,2030]" lastBlockId="29.[151,1436,153,287]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1966,1993]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Comments.</emphasis>
Like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[438,622,1966,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyacanthus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,622,1966,1994]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. oxyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the complement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[857,978,1967,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infulata">
<emphasis box="[857,978,1967,1993]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">E. infulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
description was published ahead of the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin, G." box="[551,723,2003,2029]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" pagination="135 - 153" refId="ref24439" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 a) Beitrage zur Systematik der Rhynchoten. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1904, 135 - 153." type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin 1904a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin, G." box="[736,809,2003,2029]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" pagination="49 - 50" refId="ref24467" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 b) Neue Rhynchotenausbeute aus Sud-Amerika (fortsetzung). Societas Entomologica, 19 (7), 49 - 50." type="journal article" year="1904">1904b</bibRefCitation>
, 14 June and 1 July, respectively). In both publications Breddin considered the species related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[614,770,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens">
<emphasis box="[614,631,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[644,770,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">quadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[784,984,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infulatus">
<emphasis box="[784,984,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Hypoxys infulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily separable by projected humeral angles and connexivum uniformly green, without dark spots on segments III–VI (short humeral angles and connexivum spotted in 
<emphasis box="[373,538,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName box="[373,527,224,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriden">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[373,527,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">H. quadriden</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s
</emphasis>
). The male is described here for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
